    "question_id" : 12036882,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In short: add the jar files as dependencies to your EJB project and the resulting EJB jar to your EAR project. </p>\n\n<p>You can do it differently depending on the build management system. With ant, use <code>depends</code> attribute for your targets, with maven, define the EAR project as <code>parent</code> for your EJB project. </p>\n\n<p>Ant <a href=\"http://www.java2s.com/Code/Java/EJB3/EJBTutorialfromJBossantscriptforEJBpackaging.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">example</a></p>\n\n<p>Maven <a href=\"http://www.sonatype.com/books/mvnex-book/reference/multimodule-web-spring.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">example</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 217137,
      "reputation" : 38213,
      "user_id" : 472792,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 50,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/koXXI.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Arjan Tijms",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/472792/arjan-tijms"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1345491716,
    "creation_date" : 1345491716,
    "answer_id" : 12044047,
    "question_id" : 12036882,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Jar files that are to be shared by all modules in an EAR archive can be placed in the <code>\\lib</code> folder that's in the root of the EAR.</p>\n\n<p>In Eclipse, using WTP's <code>Enterprise Application Project</code> it will look like this in project explorer:</p>\n\n<pre><code>foo_ear &lt;--- the EAR project\n    EarContent\n        lib &lt;--- Put your jars here\n            bar.jar\n            kaz.jar\nfoo_ejb &lt;--- the EJB project\n    src\n        com.example\n            Something.java\n    EAR Libraries &lt;--- lists libraries \"found\" in root EAR's /lib\n        bar.jar\n        kaz.jar\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
